2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the performance of the genetic algorithm in solving a commercial puzzle game, which is a topic that falls under game theory. 
3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The use of genetic algorithms in solving real-world problems is a topic that falls under computational engineering. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the comparison of two algorithms in terms of computational resource requirements, which is a topic that falls under software engineering. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the encoding scheme used for the genetic algorithm, which is a topic that falls under programming languages.
